timeline.message:
Eliminate Partial Marking Scheme

	In Balanced GC mode, for most of cases we use Copyforward Scheme
	(the most efficient way)to run Partial Garbage Collection. As a
	backup, Partial Marking Scheme is designed to run in case we can
	not run Copyforward Scheme( such as no enough free memory,
	JNICritical region in collection set or For generating enough
	estimate data...). Last year we introduce Copyforward MarkCompact
	Hybrid mode, which has capability to mark arbitrary regions and
	copyforward the rest of regions in collection set during PGC.
	so Copyforward MarkCompact Hybrid reduces possibility to use
	Partial Marking Scheme and also could completely replace Partial
	Marking Scheme.
	This commit try to eliminate Partial Marking Scheme(replace it
	with Copyforward MarkCompact Hybrid.

	- remove XXgc options tarokEnableCopyForwardMarkCompactHybrid and
	tarokDisableCopyForwardMarkCompactHybrid.
	- remove MM_PartialMarkDelegate, MM_PartialMarkingScheme,
	MM_PartialMarkGMPCardCleaner and MM_PartialMarkNoGMPCardCleaner.
	- keep flag _shouldRunCopyForward(when it is false) for distinguishing
	if we need to mark every collection regions.


Signed-off-by: Lin Hu <linhu@ca.ibm.com>

timeline.bodyText:
I presume tarokEnableCopyForwardHybrid flag  will be removed altogether (with a followup OMR change)? if so, referring to it in this comment does not make sense.
Also the comment referring to non-CopyForwardHybrid also should be removed, right?
Even explicitely referring to CopyForwardHybrid (as it will stay as the only mode) is redundant. The whole comment should collapse to:
"We allow eden regions, which have jniCritical, to be part of nursery collectionSet; those regions would be marked instead of copyforwarded."
timeline.author: amicic

timeline.bodyText: I remember discussing this long ago... So we agreed even if real hybrid mode was performed (there was real regions that were Marked) we will gather all relevant stats under _copyForwardStats? I think I'm ok with it, I just want to make sure that's what we agreed on and we stick with the decision everywhere (soft ref stats etc). We should probably state it somewhere in the code as well, as a comment (in declaration of _copyForwardStats in EnvVLHGC?).
